I don’t know about that - folks assume that if you play Blue you must play counters, but a counter is just a different form of answer when paired with colors that can answer pretty much any permanent. You only want your counters to deal with instants/sorceries, which none of these deal with, so they’re a different part of your answers.

I think that if you’re in blue you should probably be running at least 3 Counterspells. At times they do things that no other card can do, and that’s something that shouldn’t be overlooked. I also think that on average, Blue decks tend to play more at instant speed in general, though that obviously changes depending on the deck.
That depends on how central blue is to your deck, though. If it’s your tertiary color (in a 3-color deck) you can’t count on having the mana to cast a lot of counters.
I have 4 decks with blue and only two have counterspells
I feel like you are rewarded for playing at instant speed in Sultai than in Jund is all I mean.
That’s just a difference in deck construction then I suppose. I don’t feel comfortable not having my safety nets, and the Counterspells provide that, for me at least.
